| Review of Windows Mobile 6-Based "Wing"                            |
|   from the waitin'-for-june-29 dept.                               |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday June 05, @04:52 (Communications)    |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/05/0058255     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]opeeeerah sends us to Gundeep Hora's review of the [1]Wing, the first
Windows Mobile 6 OS-based smartphone from T-Mobile. He concludes:
"Microsoft's Windows Mobile 6 is a disappointment. Working with a number
of applications or 'heavy' documents was painful. The delay was too much,
especially in Word and PowerPoint... All in all, the T-Mobile Wing is...
a decent smartphone. If nothing else, it's an interesting gadget for the
young and hip crowd, though we wouldn't recommend it for productivity
hounds that are looking to do reports and presentations... Not to
mention, the sexy and strange appeal of the device can't be pleasing to
serious professionals. For $299.99 from T-Mobile, it's a worthy Sidekick
replacement."

