| OpenOffice.org for Mac OS X Alpha Released!                        |
|   from the copy-and-paste-how-do-you-break-that dept.              |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday June 05, @08:41 (Software)             |
|   http://apple.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/05/1152256        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Nearly 6 years after announcing a Mac port,
[0]OpenOffice.org has released the first release of OpenOffice.org for
Mac OS X that can finally run without X11!! An alpha is [1]available for
download today, but a lot of help is still needed to make OpenOffice.org
available for Mac OS X. The site is very blunt: 'WARNING: THIS SOFTWARE
MAY CRASH AND MAY DESTROY YOUR DATA DO NOT USE THIS SOFTWARE FOR REAL
WORK IN A PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT. This is an alpha test version so that
developers and users can find out what works and not, and make comments
on how to improve it.' Currently missing functionality includes printing,
pdf export, copy/pasting, and multiple monitors. That said, if you're
interested in participating you can [2]visit the Mac team to figure out
how you can help today."

