| RIAA Drops Tanya Andersen Case                                     |
|   from the pendulum-swings-both-ways dept.                         |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday June 05, @09:23 (The Courts)           |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/05/1233253          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]NewYorkCountryLawyer writes "After 2 years, the RIAA has finally
[1]dropped its longstanding case against disabled single mother Tanya
Andersen in Oregon, [2]Atlantic v. Andersen. The [3]dismissal (pdf)
relates merely to the RIAA's claims against Ms. Andersen, and does not
relate to her (a) claim for attorneys fees or (b) counterclaims against
the RIAA, which are presently before the Court on a [4]motion to dismiss.
The counterclaims were first interposed in [5]December 2005. This is the
same case in which the RIAA [6]insisted on taking a face to face
deposition of a 10 year old girl. Prior to the case, neither the mother
nor the child had ever even heard of file sharing."

