+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Terminator Gene Ban Suggested in Canada                            |
|   from the watch-out-for-those-expirey-dates dept.                 |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday June 05, @12:43 (Biotech)              |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/05/162204       |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

innocent_white_lamb writes "A member of the Canadian Parliament has
proposed legislation to [0]outlaw the development and deployment of
'terminator genes' that would prevent seeds from germinating after a set
span of time. This practice would require farmers to re-purchase seed
every year instead of saving the seeds from last year's crop. The
legislation is not expected to pass due to opposition from the
Agriculture Minister. 'There is also an issue with the technology, which
is based on a complicated five-gene construct. It is "inevitable" it will
fail and could harm biodiversity, said Lucy Sharratt, co-ordinator of the
Canadian Biotechnology Action Network, which backs the ban. CFIA argues
exactly the opposite, saying "the terminator approach provides an
excellent method to protect against transference of novel traits to other
crops and plant species."'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/05/162204

Links:
    0. http://www.cbc.ca/canada/saskatchewan/story/2007/06/01/terminator-seeds.html


