| Search for Higgs "God Particle" Gets Interesing                    |
|   from the putting-the-standard-model-to-bed dept.                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday June 05, @14:15 (Science)           |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/05/1748215      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

holy_calamity writes "The [0]Large Hadron Collider is in trouble again.
It will start work [1]sometime in spring 2008, not November this year as
planned. The delay has been blamed on an 'accumulation of minor
setbacks,' and comes on top of a 'design fault' that saw breakdown of
magnets supplied by the competing Fermilab. Yesterday Slate nicely
rounded up [2]increasingly loud rumors among physicists that Fermilab may
already have seen the Higgs particle, the 'holy grail of particle
physics' the LHC was build to find."

